'''Abdurahim Laajab''' (born 21 May 1985), commonly known as '''Ibba''', is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[association football|football]] and [[futsal]] player of [[Morocco|Moroccan]] descent who currently plays for [[V<U+00E5>lerenga Fotball|V<U+00E5>lerenga]] as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]].

Ibba played eight season at [[Adeccoligaen|second tier]] in Norway with [[Skeid Fotball|Skeid]], [[Notodden FK|Notodden]], [[Mj<U+00F8>ndalen IF|Mj<U+00F8>ndalen]] and [[Str<U+00F8>mmen IF|Str<U+00F8>mmen]] before he signed with the [[Tippeligaen]]-side V<U+00E5>lerenga in 2012. Ibba is one of the key players in the [[Norway national futsal team|Norwegian futsal team]].

==Football career==
Ibba was born to [[Morocco|Moroccan]] parents and moved to [[Norway]] when he was one month old.<ref name="DT">{{cite web |url=http://dt.no/sport/sikter-mot-tippeligaen-1.5103488 |language=Norwegian |title= Sikter mot Tippeligaen |trans_title=Aims for the Tippeliga |publisher=[[Drammens Tidende]] |date=3 April 2010 |accessdate=2012-01-09}}</ref> He played at [[V<U+00E5>lerenga Fotball|V<U+00E5>lerenga]] and [[Moss FK|Moss]] during his youth,<ref name="VG"/><ref name="altomfotball">{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2sporten.no/jsport/aof/element.do?cmd=player&personId=84602 |title=Abdurahim Laajab |language=Norwegian |work=altomfotball.no |accessdate=9 July 2012}}</ref> and later joined [[Skeid Fotball|Skeid]] because his friends were playing there.<ref name="VG">{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/sport/fotball/tippeligaen/futsalstjernen-ibba-har-signert-for-vaalerenga-3676512.html |language=Norwegian |title=Futsal-stjernen "Ibba" har signert for V<U+00E5>lerenga |trans_title=Futsal star signs with V<U+00E5>lerenga |publisher=[[TV 2 (Norway)|TV2]] |date=6 January 2012 |accessdate=9 January 2012}}</ref> At Skeid he was teammate with [[Mohammed Abdellaoue|Moa]], [[Mustafa Abdellaoue|Mos]], [[Birger Madsen]] and [[Dawda Leigh]].<ref name="DT"/>

Ibba didn't get too much playing time with Skeid, but during the second half of the 2004-season he played 248 minutes in nine matches in the [[Norwegian First Division|First Division]] and scored two goals. Ahead of the 2005-season, Ibba and his teammate Moa joined [[Rosenborg BK]] on their pre-season tour to [[La Manga]].<ref name="rbkweb">{{cite web |url=http://www.rbkweb.no/vis/3367 |language=Norwegian |title="Ibba" erstattet Madsen |publisher=RBKweb.no |date=29 Januar 2005 |accessdate=9 July 2012}}</ref> Ibba was sent on a short loan-spell to [[Dr<U+00F8>bak-Frogn IL|Dr<U+00F8>bak-Frogn]] in 2005,<ref name="altomfotball"/> and left Skeid after the season and signed a one-year contract with [[S<U+00F8>rumsand IF|S<U+00F8>rumsand]] which had been relegated from the [[Norwegian Third Division|Third Division]].<ref name="rb.no">{{cite web |url=http://www.rb.no/lokal_sport/article1937416.ece |language=Norwegian |title=Fra S<U+00F8>rumsand til tysk storklubb |trans_title=From S<U+00F8>rumsand to big German club |publisher=[[Romerikes Blad]] |date=3 February 2006 |accessdate=9 January 2012}}</ref>

Before he played a match for S<U+00F8>rumsand, Ibba moved to [[Borussia M<U+00F6>nchengladbach]]<ref name="rb.no"/> where [[J<U+00F8>rn Andersen]] was the assistant coach. Ibba and Andersen communicated with eachother in Norwegian. A year later Andersen was fired together with the head coach, and the new coach only talked to Ibba in German, a language Ibba did not try to learn, and eventually Ibba requested to terminate his contract and moved home to Norway.<ref name="DT"/> He only played one match for [[Borussia M<U+00F6>nchengladbach II]].<ref name="transfermarkt">[http://www.transfermarkt.co.uk/en/abdurahim-laajaab/leistungsdaten-vereindetail/spieler_37967_1006.html Adurahim Laajab] at transfermarkt.co.uk</ref>

In 2007 Ibba was back in Skeid, before he signed a contract with [[Notodden FK|Notodden]] ahead of the 2008-season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ta.no/lokal_sport/article3322494.ece |language=Norwegian |title=Ibba signerte - Notodden tapte |work=ta.no |publisher=Telemarksavisa |date=1 February 2008 |accessdate=9 July 2012}}</ref> Ibba played regularly in the first-team until head coach [[Jan Halvor Halvorsen]] was fired halfway through the 2009-season. The new coach, [[Arne Sandst<U+00F8>]] placed him on the bench and Ibba left the club after the season. Ahead of the 2010-season, Ibba was on a trial with the Spanish second-tier club [[Elche CF|Elche]] and was offered a contract there, but Ibba rejected the offer and decided to move to [[Mj<U+00F8>ndalen IF|Mj<U+00F8>ndalen]] instead.<ref name="DT"/> Mj<U+00F8>ndalen's coach [[Vegard Hansen]] stated that Ibba was a risky signing due to his poor reputation, but that the 24-year had a such an unredeemed potential that he couldn't ignore him.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dt.no/sport/mif/abdurahim-laajaab-signerte-med-mif-1.3043029 |language=Norwegian |title=Abdurahim Laajaab signerte med MIF |publisher=Drammens Tidende |date=25 January 2010 |accessdate=9 July 2012}}</ref>

Ibba played for [[Str<U+00F8>mmen IF|Str<U+00F8>mmen]] in 2011, where he scored seven goals in 24 matches in [[Adeccoligaen]],<ref name="Nettavisen">{{cite web |url=http://www.nettavisen.no/sport/fotball/article3306470.ece |language=Norwegian |title=V<U+00E5>lerenga signerte "futsalstjerne" |trans_title=Futsal star signed with V<U+00E5>lerenga |publisher=[[Nettavisen]] |date=6 January 2012 |accessdate=9 January 2012}}</ref> and ahead of the 2012-season he signed for V<U+00E5>lerenga.<ref name="VG"/><ref name="bt.no">{{cite web |url=http://fotball.bt.no/eliteserien/article218665.ece |language=Norwegian |title=VIF-Andresen signerte futsal-stjerne |trans_title=Andresen signed futsal star |publisher=[[Bergens Tidende]] |work=[[Norwegian News Agency|NTB]] |date=6 January 2012 |accessdate=9 January 2012}}</ref> After Ibba's transfer to V<U+00E5>lerenga, his former team mate from Skeid and former V<U+00E5>lerenga-player, Moa, said in an interview with [[TV 2 (Norway)|Norwegian TV2]] that the supporters of V<U+00E5>lerenga should be excited about their new signing and dubbed Ibba as one of the best newcomers of the [[2012 Tippeligaen]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/sport/fotball/tippeligaen/moa-ingen-andre-kan-det-ibba-kan-3726862.html |language=Norwegian |title=Moa: <U+2013> Ingen andre kan det Ibba kan! |trans_title=Moa: <U+2013> Noone else can do what Ibba does! |publisher=[[TV 2 (Norway)|TV2]] |date=8 March 2012 |accessdate=4 July 2012}}</ref> Ibba made his first-team debut for V<U+00E5>lerenga in the friendly match against the [[Norwegian Second Division|Second Division]]-side [[Nesodden IF|Nesodden]] on 11 January 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/sport/fotball/tippeligaen/ibba-faar-sin-vifdebut-3680398.html |language=Norwegian |title=Ibba f<U+00E5>r sin VIF-debut |work=tv2.no |publisher=[[TV 2 (Norway)|TV2]] |date=11 January 2012 |accessdate=9 July 2012}}</ref> 

==Futsal career==
Ibba is known as one of the biggest futsal-star in Norway.<ref name="VG"/><ref name="Nettavisen"/><ref name="bt.no"/> In his debut for the [[Norway national futsal team|Norwegian futsal team]], he scored three goals when Norway won 7-2 against [[Malta national futsal team|Malta]] on 13 January 2011.<ref name="Dagbladet">{{cite web |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/2011/01/14/sport/fotball/futsal/norge/15063898/ |language=Norwegian |title="Ibba" lekte inn tre m<U+00E5>l i debuten for Norge |trans_title=Ibba easily scored three goals in his national team debut |publisher=[[Dagbladet]] |date=14 January 2011|accessdate=9 January 2012}}</ref> The next day he again scored three goals against Malta, before he scored another hat-trick when Norway won against [[Israel national futsal team|Israel]] in the [[2012 UEFA Futsal Championship qualifying|qualifying match]] for the [[2012 UEFA Futsal Championship]] on 20 January, which made a total of nine goals in his first three matches for Norway.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/2011/01/21/sport/fotball/futsal/futsallandslaget/15150379/ |language=Norwegian |title=<U+00AB>Ibba<U+00BB> har gjort tre hattrick p<U+00E5> sine tre landskamper |publisher=Dagbladet |date=21 January 2011|accessdate=9 July 2012}}</ref>

Ahead of the [[2012 FIFA Futsal World Cup qualification (UEFA)|qualifying]] match against [[Spain national futsal team|Spain]] on 15 December 2011, Norway's national team coach [[Espen O. S<U+00E6>ther]] called Ibba a "top international futsal player", and that if their chances against Spain was depending on Ibba's performance and that he had to play at his very best.<ref name="TV2">{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/sport/fotball/tippeligaen/landslagssjefen-om-ibba-han-er-paa-et-internasjonalt-toppnivaa-3661461.html |language=Norwegian |title=Landslagssjefen om "Ibba": <U+2013> Han er p<U+00E5> et internasjonalt toppniv<U+00E5> |trans_title=National team manager about "Ibba": "He is at a top international level" |publisher=[[TV 2 (Norway)|TV2]] |date=15 December 2011 |accessdate=9 January 2012}}</ref> Three days later, Ibba scored the goal that secured a 3-3 draw against [[Belgium national futsal team|Belgium]] and sent Norway to the playoff round of the [[2012 FIFA Futsal World Cup]] qualifier.<ref name="bt.no"/> 

==Style of play==
Laajab has a good physique, a good temperament and good one-on-one skills and has a great breakthrough force.<ref name="vif-fotball">{{Cite web |url=http://www.vif-fotball.no/article3350120.ece |language=Norwegian |title=Style of playing |publisher=vif-fotball.no |date=6 April 2012|accessdate=6 April 2012}}{{deadlink}}</ref>

